If each angle measures 90 degrees and one angle measures twice the other, let $a$ be the measure of the smaller angle.  Then the larger angle measures $2a$, so the sum of the measures of the $4$ angles is $90+90+2a+a=180+3a$, so $180+3a=360$.  Then $3a=180$ and $a=60$ degrees.  The measure of the largest angle is $2a=2(60)=\boxed{120}$ degrees.กรุงเทพ
