Let $x = \tan 100^\circ.$  Then from the angle addition formula,
\[x + \sin 100^\circ = \frac{\tan 100^\circ + \sin 100^\circ}{\cos 100^\circ} = \frac{x}{\cos 100^\circ}.\]From the angle subtraction formula,
\[\cos 100^\circ = \cos (90^\circ - 100^\circ) = -\sin 100^\circ.\]Therefore, $x = -x^2.$  The only real number that satisfies this equation is $x = -1.$  So,
\[\tan 100^\circ + 4 \sin 100^\circ = -1 + 4 \sin 100^\circ = -1 + 4 \cdot \frac{1 - \cos 100^\circ}{2} = -1 + 2 - 2 \cos 100^\circ = \boxed{1 - 2 \cos 100^\circ}.\](Note that this value equals $1.$)尿
